author: The Record
title: H.S. girls volleyball notebook: Oct. 6, 2015 - Girls Volleyball
text:
SHOWDOWN: In what could be a preview of the Bergen girls volleyball final, No. 2 NV/Old Tappan hosts No. 1 Immaculate Heart at 5:30 p.m. Wednesday, with the winner almost certain to receive the top seed for the county tournament. Immaculate Heart, the four-time reigning Tournament of Champions titlist, owns a 93-match winning streak against Garden State foes.
COPPER STATE OF MIND: Immaculate Heart (17-4) won three of seven matches in its debut at last week's Nike Tournament of Champions, which featured national powerhouses. The Blue Eagles' trip to Arizona included a win over New York rival St. Mary's.
"We stepped out of our comfort zone in New Jersey and accepted the challenge," coach Maria Nolan said, "and luckily it paid off."
PANTHER PURSUIT: Wallington transformed the NJIC Meadowlands Division into a four-team race with a 17-25, 25-13, 27-25 victory Thursday that ended Becton's two-season, 25-match division winning streak. The Wildcats survived five match points, beginning with senior Angelica Urban's kill and ending with senior Sam Kruk (16 digs) serving the final two points.
T-BIRDS KEEP RISING: Weekend wars have helped No. 9 Mahwah (9-2) build an eight-game winning streak featuring a 25-23, 25-23 upset over Ramapo. Senior S Britni Jaskot, senior L Olivia Brand, senior H Karina Almeda, junior M Tabitha Paul and sophomore H Caelin Jaskot helped the T-Birds make strong showings at three weekend tournaments.
"I think those weekends gave us some confidence that we didn't have when we started the season," coach Dean Rayside said.
QUICKS: Fort Lee's John Ziemba, who has more than 300 coaching wins in boys basketball, earned his 200th in volleyball with Thursday's 25-16, 25-12 victory over Ramsey. … Immaculate Heart hosts the prestigious Garden State Challenge on Saturday and Sunday at Fairleigh Dickinson's Rothman Center in Hackensack, and teams from New York, Pennsylvania and Maryland will join a Garden State contingent that includes Bogota, Hunterdon Central, Ridge and Cherokee. … Rutherford (8-3) rejoins The Record girls volleyball Top 20 in the final spot after winning eight of its past nine matches. Senior Jessica Rogers has totaled 176 kills, an average of seven per set. … Passaic's first victory of the season came at Hawthorne Christian in Thursday's Passaic County tournament opener, 28-26, 25-17. … Paterson Charter earned its first victory of the season, 25-21, 25-18, over American History in a non-league match Friday. … Standings for the Big North and NJIC can be found on the Varsity Aces' Web page: northjersey.com/varsityaces.
— Greg Mattura
